Optional.  The stable unique identifier your organization uses to identifiy this variant. Although optional, it is highly recommended you assign this value.

Required. This value is used to connect a row on the Variant tab to one or more rows in the CaseData tab. If each variant is submitted once on the Variant tab, you can use the HGVS as the Linking ID. If any variant is submitted more than once on the Variant tab (with more than one condition), the Linking ID should be specific to that variant-condition pair.
Optional.  This must be the preferred symbol from HGNC. Multiple separated by semi-colon.
Required if Genomic coordinates are not provided. The reference sequence for the variant description in the HGVS name column, e.g. NM_000492.3, NG_016465.3, NC_000007.13.

Required for sequence variants if genomic coordinates are not provided.

(http://www.hgvs.org/mutnomen/examplesDNA.html, http://www.hgvs.org/mutnomen/standards.html). Required if Reference sequence is not provided.  If you submit genomic coordinates, you must also provide the name of the genome assembly on the SubmissionInfo tab. This will be used to validate the calculation of genomic location based on the combination of Reference sequence and HGVS name.

Report as database name:database identifier; integers without a database name cannot be processed. Separate multiple identifiers by semi-colon. Examples: PROBE:Pr153103;
SRA:SRX073508; TRACE:FJ043059

Optional. To identify simple variants vs complex variants. Simple is the default value. Other allowed values are complex (multiple changes that are considered a single variant); haplotype (multiple independent variants in cis); and compound (multiple independent variants in trans).

Optional.  Any of OMIM allelic variant ID, dbSNP rs number, dbVar submitter or region identifier, Swiss-Prot VAR id. Optional.  This can be used for intron or exon number. These must be submitted with the reference sequence used to define the numbering system, e.g.  NM_000060.2:exon 2.
Optional.  A set of alternative,  common, or legacy names for the variant, or an alternate HGVS expression, e.g. for protein. Separate multiple names by vertical bar.

Optional.  A URL that points to this variant on your organization's website.

Required if "Preferred condition name" is not supplied. Please specify the type of Condition ID supplied in the Condition ID value column. Values may include both diseases and phenotypes  Allowed values are: OMIM, MeSH, MedGen, UMLS, HPO.  If you use a different ontology, please check with us first.

Required if "Preferred condition name" is not supplied. Please specify the identifer from the database referenced in the Condition ID type column. If there are multiple values, they all need to be from the same source, and delimited by a semicolon.
Defaults to Disease if not filled in. Allowed spreadsheet values are Disease, DrugResponse, BloodGroup, Finding.  Use Finding for clinical findings with no disease diagnosis.

Required if "Condition ID Type" and "Condition ID Value" are not supplied.  We strongly encourage describing condition by specific identifiers. If this is not feasible, you may list the observed conditions here, delimited by a vertical bar. If you do not wish to make an assertion about condition, please enter "not provided."  In cases where the Clinical significance is "benign" and no condition is associated with the variant, you may use "AllHighlyPenetrant" as the condition.

Required: Clinical significance is required. One option, however, is ‘not provided’, so submitters are not required to calculate significance to submit their data. Allowed values: Pathogenic, Likely pathogenic, Uncertain significance, Likely benign, Benign, association, drug response, confers sensitivity, protective, risk factor, other, not provided. If "other" or "drug response", please expand "Clinical Significance - more" columns.

column1: Explanation if clinical significance is other or drug response
column2:
Required if 'other' is selected for clinical significance: Submitter's  clinical significance.  Please contact us regarding the  new value.  

Optional for clinical significance of  "drug response".  Allows a  submitter value describing  the drug response.  

These values should be short for display purposes.
Optional.  The disease or condition for which the drug response is relevant.

Required, if available: date the clinical significance was last evaluated.  If not available, leave blank.  If  only month/year is provided we will convert it to the first day of the month.  If only year is provided it will be converted to the first day of the first month of the year.

Optional.  Supported values are from the Human Phenotype Ontology (HPO). Allowed values include: Autosomal dominant inheritance, Autosomal recessive inheritance, Autosomal unknown, Codominant, Genetic anticipation, Mitochondrial inheritance, Sex-limited autosomal dominant, Somatic mutation, Sporadic,  X-linked inheritance, Y-linked inheritance, Other.  If you provide Other, please specify, e.g. Other:new mode of inheritance.  NOTE:  This mode of inheritance value is relative to the variation, not to the disease.

Optional.  Citations documenting the clinical significance. Any of PubMed, PubMedCentral, DOI, NCBI Bookshelf combined with the id in that database (e.g. PMID:123456).  Multiples separated by a semicolon.
Optional, but highly encouraged.  Free text describing the rationale for the clinical significance.

Optional. Used to describe the effect of the variation with respect to the function of the gene product. May include loss of function, reduced activity with quantitative values, novel splicing, etc. Allowed values are Sequence Ontology (http://www.sequenceontology.org/browser/obob.cgi) and VariO (http://www.variationontology.org/cgi-bin/amivario/browse.cgi) terms, e.g. SO:1000071, VariO:0397. Multiples separated by a semicolon.
Required: Type of approach in this method. Allowed values: case-control, clinical testing, literature only, in vitro, in vivo, reference population, research.
Required: The genetic origin of  the variant. Allowed values:  germline, somatic,  unknown.
Required: Indicate whether or not the individual(s) had the condition. Allowed values: yes, no, unknown.
Optional. Tissue sampled to assay the variation. Highly recommended for somatic variants. Free text.
Optional. Sex of individuals sampled. Allowed values: female, male, mixed gender group. To submit sex-specific values, use one line for each.

Optional. The range of ages at time of testing for individuals included in this sample, with units. If age range is an important variable in your submission, with different observations based on the age, please submit each observation separately, rather than lumping into one summary observation with one sample description. For prenatal testing, use number of months gestation. For ages <1 year, use number of months. For ages over 85 years, please report >85 years, not the specific age.
